article.linkText: Whitney-Sidney scores 22 as Lehigh takes down Army 85-54
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- — Tyler Whitney-Sidney scored 22 points as Lehigh beat Army 85-54 on Wednesday night. Whitney-Sidney shot 8 for 11 (2 for 3 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free throw line for the Mountain Hawks (11-15, 8-7 Patriot League). Dominic Parolin added 18 points while going 7 of 11 from the floor, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and 3 for 3 from the line, and he also had 10 rebounds. Keith Higgins Jr. had 14 points and shot 4 for 5 (2 for 3 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free throw line. Abe Johnson, Josh Scovens and Jorn Everson scored eight points each for the Black Knights (10-18, 6-9). ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
